In England, in the seven days to 15 September, there were 146,616 new confirmed cases (259.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 September, there were 188,573 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 22% (41,957 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 September is 6,374,123 (11,271.6 cases per 100,000 population).
